modules.description: Handles parsing and manipulation of MTRT format data, including message decoding and header extraction. Works with binary buffers and structured data representations of network routing information. Used to process raw network traffic logs and generate human-readable route summaries.

Converts header and payload data structures to string representations, and parses a Cstruct into a structured format. Operates on custom types representing network headers, payloads, and combined message structures. Used to serialize and deserialize network message components during protocol processing.
